Tea with Strangers: OverviewThe idea behind the "Tea with Strangers" project is simple. We take our tea sets, go sit in public places (parks, squares, streets, etc.), prepare tea according to Chinese traditions, and invite complete strangers to join us for a cup of tea! We offer the tea for free, but in return we ask strangers to share an interesting story from their life. We share our stories, they share theirs. People leave, we’ll probably never see them again. They continue their way, we stay and greet new strangers. Same-same, but different. Different stories, different lives.The stories and the photographs that we collect during our tea ceremonies, are later published on our website and Facebook page, so that others can follow the stories of strangers we meet and share tea with.​Initially, the project was started in Yerevan, the capital of Armenia. But we hope to travel to other cities and other countries, and collect stories there, too. So far we’ve visited the cities of Gyumri and Etchmiadzin in Armenia, and Isfahan, Iran.Our aim is to erase any borders between people who may seem to be strangers to each other, but we’re all water from different rivers after all.Our project came to life thanks to the Awesome Foundation Yerevan Chapter. The initial funds of $1000 we were granted were used to purchase all the necessary items for a traditional Chinese tea ceremony (several tea pots, cups, tea ceremony deck, instruments, etc.) as well as various types of Chinese tea. We also purchased a portable gas stove.But since we never ask strangers to pay for the tea we offer to them, we cover all the expenses ourselves. And as the project grows, we need your support to keep it alive and develop it.The funds raised will be used for the following purpose:
Design and production of "Tea with Strangers" booklet or a zine (we want to print the stories and photos in the format of a zine or a booklet and distribute it for free to strangers who join our gatherings);
Web hosting service (our website is currently hosted on a free hosting website, we want to move a paid hosting and also hire an expert web designer to help us improve the website itself);
Voice recorder (we hold the tea ceremonies in public areas, and it is often very noisy around, so we need a good voice recorder to record the stories that strangers share with us);
We want to purchase a portable table for tea ceremonies as well as a suitcase that we'll use to carry all of the tea ceremony items;
Larger clay tea pots (more and more people attend our gatherings, and we realized we need larger tea pots to brew tea);
New tea ceremony items and tools to replace the damaged ones;
Tea (and finally, we constantly need to purchase Chinese tea for our tea ceremonies).

Other Ways You Can Help:

If you can donate us one of the items mentioned above, that's even better!
Or maybe you can help us with our website? 
Spread the word. You can help us by sharing the campaign among your friends.

